-- France’s Bouygues May Help Build Croatian Bridge, Poslovni Says
-- B y   J a s m i n a   K u z m a n o v i c
-- 2012-12-07T07:43:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-07/france-s-bouygues-may-help-build-croatian-bridge-poslovni-says.html
Bouygues SA (EN) , French construction and
utilities manager, is interested in building the Peljesac bridge
in  Croatia ,  Poslovni Dnevnik  reported, citing Charles Paradis,
the company’s construction director.  The  Croatian government  in August said it revived a plan to
build a bridge connecting the southernmost resort of Dubrovnik
with the rest of the country. The project’s cost is estimated at
about 2 billion kuna ($344 million) and may be financed by the
European Union.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jasmina Kuzmanovic in Zagreb at 
 jkuzmanovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  